  <description><![CDATA[<p>Situated on in the heart of the Corso dell’Imperatrice, the Hotel Lolli Palace has been run by the Lolli family since 1938. Surrounded by palm trees gifted to the region by former Russian Empress Maria Alexandrovna, the hotel is set in a breath taking Art Nouveau villa and its roof top terrace boasts some of the finest views in Sanremo with panoramic views of the surrounding bays. It exudes the old time luxury for which the resort is so well known, the neighbouring French Riviera and Montecarlo just over 18 miles away influencing the local architecture and cuisine alike.</p>
<p>Chefs at the onsite Liberty Restaurant pride themselves on creating a rich menu showcasing the finest ingredients Liguria has to offer. Chef Valeriano and his team combine traditional and modern dishes fresh from the sea for you to enjoy in the lavishly furnished dining room or on the charming roof garden with sprawling sea views. Should you wish to go further afield to explore the town, the Corso dell’Imperatrice district certainly has no shortage of fabulous restaurants, bars and cafes.</p>]]></description>
